To show this, we will use the fact that $\tan^2 \theta = \frac{\sin^2 \theta}{\cos^2 \theta} = \frac{1 - \cos^2 \theta}{\cos^2 \theta}$.

First, square both given equations and add them:
\begin{align*}
(\cos^2 x + \cos^2 y + \cos^2 z) + 2(\cos x \cos y + \cos x \cos z + \cos y \cos z) &= 0^2, \\
(\sin^2 x + \sin^2 y + \sin^2 z) + 2(\sin x \sin y + \sin x \sin z + \sin y \sin z) &= 0^2.
\end{align*}
Since $\cos^2 \theta + \sin^2 \theta = 1$, we have
\begin{align*}
1 + 1 + 1 + 2(\cos x \cos y + \cos x \cos z + \cos y \cos z) &= 0, \\
1 + 1 + 1 + 2(\sin x \sin y + \sin x \sin z + \sin y \sin z) &= 0.
\end{align*}
Subtracting these equations, we get
\begin{align*}
2(\cos x \cos y + \cos x \cos z + \cos y \cos z - \sin x \sin y - \sin x \sin z - \sin y \sin z) &= 0.
\end{align*}
Using the angle subtraction formula, we have
\begin{align*}
\cos x \cos y - \sin x \sin y &= \cos(x + y), \\
\cos x \cos z - \sin x \sin z &= \cos(x + z), \\
\cos y \cos z - \sin y \sin z &= \cos(y + z).
\end{align*}
Thus, we have
\begin{align*}
\cos(x + y) + \cos(x + z) + \cos(y + z) &= 0.
\end{align*}
Now, we will compute the desired expression:
\begin{align*}
&\tan^2 x + \tan^2 y + \tan^2 z - (\tan^2 x \tan^2 y + \tan^2 x \tan^2 z + \tan^2 y \tan^2 z) \\
&\quad  - 3 \tan^2 x \tan^2 y \tan^2 z \\
&= \frac{1 - \cos^2 x}{\cos^2 x} + \frac{1 - \cos^2 y}{\cos^2 y} + \frac{1 - \cos^2 z}{\cos^2 z} \\
&\quad - \frac{(1 - \cos^2 x)(1 - \cos^2 y)}{\cos^2 x \cos^2 y} - \frac{(1 - \cos^2 x)(1 - \cos^2 z)}{\cos^2 x \cos^2 z} - \frac{(1 - \cos^2 y)(1 - \cos^2 z)}{\cos^2 y \cos^2 z} \\
&\quad - 3 \frac{(1 - \cos^2 x)(1 - \cos^2 y)(1 - \cos^2 z)}{\cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z}.
\end{align*}
Multiplying the numerator and denominator of each term by the appropriate power of $\cos x \cos y \cos z$, we get
\begin{align*}
&\phantom{=} \frac{(1 - \cos^2 x)(\cos^2 y \cos^2 z) + (\cos^2 x)(1 - \cos^2 y)(\cos^2 z) + (\cos^2 x \cos^2 y)(1 - \cos^2 z)}{(\cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z)} \\
&\quad - \frac{(1 - \cos^2 x)(1 - \cos^2 y)(\cos^2 x \cos^2 y + \cos^2 x \cos^2 z + \cos^2 y \cos^2 z)}{(\cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z)^2} \\
&\quad - 3 \frac{(1 - \cos^2 x)(1 - \cos^2 y)(1 - \cos^2 z)}{(\cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z)^2}.
\end{align*}
Now, note that
\begin{align*}
&(1 - \cos^2 x)(\cos^2 y \cos^2 z) + (\cos^2 x)(1 - \cos^2 y)(\cos^2 z) + (\cos^2 x \cos^2 y)(1 - \cos^2 z) \\
&\quad = (\cos^2 y \cos^2 z - \cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z) + (\cos^2 x \cos^2 z - \cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z) + (\cos^2 x \cos^2 y - \cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z) \\
&\quad = \cos^2 y \cos^2 z + \cos^2 x \cos^2 z + \cos^2 x \cos^2 y - 3 \cos^2 x \cos^2 y \cos^2 z.
\end{align*}
Thus, the desired expression is
